 of Chi Ren (遲任), a person who lived during the Shang dynasty (1600–1046  BC ). (ii) shortened form of the Chinese compound surname Yu-Chi (尉遲), originally the name of a tribe from the Xianbei ethnic group in northern China. (iii) from the second element of the personal name Zi Chi (子遲), style name of Fan Xu, a student of Confucius (551–479  BC )."]}]},{"name":"Letitia","type":"FIRST","attribution":"Dictionary of First Names © Patrick Hanks and Flavia Hodges 1990, 2003, 2006.","meanings":["Simplified spelling of   Laetitia  , which has recently enjoyed a rise in popularity in Britain, notably among West Indians."],"variants":[]}],"lifeSummary":"Letitia di Manoppello was born about 1130, in Italy as the daughter of Conte Boemondo di Manoppello. She had at least 1 daughter with Pietro di Palearia."},"et":{"about 1130–":"umbes 1130–Surnud","1130–Female":"1130–Surnud","1125–1183":"1125–1183","1155–Female":"1155–Surnud","1100–1169":"1100–1169","1169":"1169","1125":"1125","1100":"1100","1155":"1155","1130":"1130","1183":"1183","about 1155":"umbes 1155","about 1130":"umbes 1130","Italy":"Itaalia"},"fi":{"about 1130–":"noin 1130–Kuollut","1130–Female":"1130–Kuollut","1125–1183":"1125–1183","1155–Female":"1155–Kuollut","1100–1169":"1100–1169","1169":"1169","1125":"1125","1100":"1100","1155":"1155","1130":"1130","1183":"1183","about 1155":"noin 1155","about 1130":"noin 1130","Italy":"Italia"},"fr":{"about 1130–":"environ 1130–Décédée","1130–Female":"1130–Décédée","1125–1183":"1125–1183","1155–Female":"1155–Décédée","1100–1169":"1100–1169","1169":"1169","1125":"1125","1100":"1100","1155":"1155","1130":"1130","1183":"1183","about 1155":"environ 1155","about 1130":"environ 1130","Italy":"Italie","lifeSummary":"Letitia di Manoppello est née environ 1130, à Italie, fille de Conte Boemondo di Manoppello. Elle a eu au moins 1 fille avec Pietro di Palearia."},"de":{"about 1130–":"um 1130–Verstorben","1130–Female":"1130–Verstorben","1125–1183":"1125–1183","1155–Female":"1155–Verstorbe